# File Structure

## Directory map
- `css/styles.css` — Global styles, variables, nav, buttons, hero, modal
- `css/docs.css` — Docs layout only (sidebar, TOC, code blocks)
- `css/pages.css` — All non-index, non-docs pages (pricing, legal, auth, security, contact)
- `js/nav.js` — Shared nav logic, dark mode, waitlist modal. Loaded on EVERY page.
- `js/main.js` — Landing page specific logic only
- `js/docs.js` — Docs pages only. Always loaded AFTER nav.js
- `index.html` — Homepage, root level
- `pages/` — All other HTML pages (pricing, contact, security, privacy, terms, signin)
- `pages/docs/` — All docs pages
- `images/` — Static assets only

## Placement rules
- New CSS goes in `styles.css` unless it is docs-specific or page-specific
- New HTML pages go in `pages/` unless they are the homepage
- New docs pages go in `pages/docs/`
- Never create new CSS or JS files without asking first
- Never create files in the root except `index.html`, `package.json`, `test.js`, and config files

## Link format rules
- All links in `pages/` and `pages/docs/` must use absolute paths starting with `/`
- Example: `/css/styles.css`, `/js/nav.js`, `/pages/pricing.html`, `/pages/docs/index.html`
- Never use relative links like `../` or `pricing.html` in nav or footer

## Every HTML page must include
- `<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css"/>`
- `<script src="/js/nav.js"></script>`
- The waitlist modal block
- The standard nav and footer

## Every docs page (`pages/docs/*.html`) must also include
- `<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/docs.css"/>`
- `<script src="/js/docs.js"></script>` (after nav.js)
- `id="docs-sidebar"` on the sidebar
- `id="sidebar-toggle"` button
- The full sidebar nav block (all 4 sections)